# Design System

## Palette (CSS variables in `app/globals.css`, exposed via Tailwind v4 `@theme inline`)

| Token         | Hex       | Tailwind class    | Use                                      |
| ------------- | --------- | ----------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `--bg`        | `#F2E8DE` | `bg-bg`           | page background (warm beige)             |
| `--text`      | `#3C2E22` | `text-text`       | body copy                                |
| `--link`      | `#7D623F` | `text-link`       | links, secondary text                    |
| `--accent`    | `#AD473B` | `text-accent`     | red accent (headlines, CTAs)             |
| `--border`    | `#C39367` | `border-border`   | hairline borders, button outlines        |
| `--dark`      | `#2A1F17` | `bg-dark`         | dark overlays / footer                   |
| `--cream`     | `#FAF4EB` | `bg-cream`        | lifted surfaces                          |

## Typography (loaded via `next/font` in `app/layout.tsx`)

- Display: **Cormorant Garamond** (serif) → `font-display` (`var(--font-display)`). Use for headlines.
- Body: **Inter** (sans) → `font-sans` (`var(--font-sans)`). Use for everything else.
- Nav links are rendered **lowercase** (`lowercase tracking-wide`).

## Header (Uchi-style)

- Fixed `top-0 left-0 w-full z-50`. **Single** height: **70px mobile / 96px desktop**. Do **not** add a separate "scrolled" / "compact" state — the only motion is the hide/reveal transform.
- Always opaque on `bg-bg` with `border-b border-border/80`.
- **Hide on scroll-down**, **reveal on scroll-up** — only one animated property: `transform` between `translate-y-0` and `-translate-y-full`. Threshold: don't hide before ~120px of scroll, ignore scroll deltas under 6px to avoid flicker. Drawer open keeps the bar visible (`openPanel` blocks hide).
- Logo left, lowercase inline nav center/right (hidden under `lg`), bordered "reservations" CTA far right, hamburger under `lg`.

## Buttons

- **Bordered (primary CTA on header / hero):** `border border-border text-text hover:bg-dark hover:text-bg transition-colors px-6 py-2 lowercase tracking-wide`.
- **Underline link CTA (sections):** `underline underline-offset-4 hover:no-underline lowercase tracking-wide text-bg`.

## Sections (Avalaun-style full-bleed scroll)

Full-bleed sections scroll **normally** (no sticky stack). Each is its own `min-h-screen` panel; sections are visually separated by a [`SectionBreak`](app/_components/SectionBreak.tsx) breaker on the `bg-bg` warm-beige strip.

The image inside each section gets a **JS-driven parallax** via [`ParallaxImage`](app/_components/ParallaxImage.tsx) — a single `requestAnimationFrame`-throttled scroll handler measures the **section's** `getBoundingClientRect` (not the wrapper's, to avoid feedback from its own transform) and translates the image wrapper opposite to the scroll direction at `intensity` (default `0.35`). Respects `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`. Works in every browser — don't reach for `animation-timeline: view()` (Safari/Firefox don't support it yet).

Rules:

- Each `<Section>` outer is `relative isolate flex min-h-screen w-full items-center overflow-hidden`. Normal flow — no `position: sticky`, no `h-screen`.
- The image wrapper inside `ParallaxImage` is `absolute inset-x-0 -top-[30%] h-[160%]` so the ±~30vh parallax translate never exposes seams. Don't shrink this without lowering `intensity`.
- Sections are direct siblings under `<main>`; place a `<SectionBreak label="..." />` between adjacent sections in [`app/page.tsx`](app/page.tsx).
- Don't add `overflow: hidden` on `html` / `body` — it kills `getBoundingClientRect`-based scroll math when the body is the scroller.

Markup of a single section (handled by [`Section`](app/_components/sections/Section.tsx)):

```tsx
<section className="relative isolate flex min-h-screen w-full items-center overflow-hidden text-bg">
  <ParallaxImage src={...} alt="" />
  <div className="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-dark/55" />
  <div className="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl px-6 text-center">
    <h2 className="font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl">...</h2>
  </div>
</section>
```

## Easing

Use `cubic-bezier(0.355, 0.820, 0.335, 1)` for header / nav transitions (matches the Uchi reference). Available as `ease-uchi` via custom Tailwind utility.
